cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.SY, cs.NI, cs.CR 

This paper discusses a new framework for workload partitioning in parallel stream processing engines, which involves optimizing the distribution of workload among worker threads. This topic is closely related to distributed computing (cs.DC), database systems (cs.DB), and system and control theory (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper proposes algorithms for dynamic workload assignment, which involves network communication and optimization, making it relevant to networked systems (cs.NI) and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
